Telkom has released its integrated report for the year ended 31 March 2018. The report contains an overview of the company’s performance and further details on previous financial results which have been released. Telkom has also disclosed how much its top executives earn, as part of a remuneration disclosure section in the document. Telkom Group CEO Sipho Maseko took home an effective R27.1 million, which was up up of his guaranteed package and other benefits. Former Telkom CFO Deon Fredericks, who recently left his position, earned a package of R13.5 million. The remuneration of Telkom’s executives, for the year ended 31 March 2018, is detailed in the table below.